description:
src/delivery.rs:27-31 — CircuitBreaker::new() is a plain constructor that creates an empty HashMap:

    fn new() -> Self {
        Self { failures: HashMap::new() }
    }

Per standards: 'Default where there is an obvious zero/empty state.' This type has a clear empty state and should derive or impl Default, allowing Arc::new(Mutex::new(CircuitBreaker::default())).

Impact: Minor idiom violation. Default is a standard Rust signal that a type has a meaningful zero value.
